# Storyboard Output Format
 
## Template
 
```
## STORYBOARD: [Product] — [Platform] [Duration]
Total Length: [Xs] | Total Frames: [N] @ 30fps | Elements: [#] | Scenes: [#]
Dimensions: [W×H] | Tone: [style] | Arc: [A/B/C/D / Cinematic]
UI Source: [TSX from HTML / Screenshots / Screen recording / None]
Architecture: [A — Camera-based / B — Frame-based]
 
---
 
### SCENE [N]: [SCENE NAME]
 
### ELEMENT [N] ([start]–[end]) | Frames: [FROM]–[TO] | durationInFrames: [N]
 
VO/Audio: "[exact words or sound cue]"
Visual: [description]
Shot Type: [Wide / Medium / Close / Screen / TSX UI / Animation / AI-gen]
Source: [TSX (from HTML) / Screen recording / Stock / AI-gen / Screenshot / Remotion]
 
[Source-specific block — only include the relevant one:]
 
If TSX (from HTML):
  Component: [ComponentName]
  Highlight: [sub-section to zoom into]
  Interaction: [animation behavior]
 
If Stock:
  Keywords: [search terms]
 
If AI-gen:
  Prompt: "[full generation prompt]"
 
If Screen:
  Notes: [flow to record]
 
Text Overlay: "[on-screen text]"
Text Animation: [Fade / Pop / Slide-up / Velocity-slide / Typewriter / Glitch / None]
Transition to next: [Cut / Fade / Dissolve / Slide / Scale / Wipe]
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Entry: [e.g. opacity 0→1 over frames 0–12]
  - Motion: [e.g. translateY 30→0 over frames 0–20, easeOut]
  - Exit: [e.g. scale 1→1.05 + opacity 1→0 over frames 80–90]
  - Key hooks: [interpolate / spring / useVideoTexture / etc.]
 
---
 
### PRODUCTION NOTES
Music: [style, BPM, mood]
Pacing: [Fast / Medium / Breathing / Mixed — describe the arc]
Color: [brand-matched / cinematic dark / warm / cool]
Style: [Polished SaaS / Native / Cinematic / B2B]
Captions: [required / optional]
 
### REMOTION SCAFFOLD
[Full file structure, composition config, scene frame map, asset checklist]
```
 
---
 
## Worked Example: App Intro (30s, LinkedIn 16:9, TSX UI)
 
```
## STORYBOARD: Atlas — LinkedIn 30s App Intro
Total Length: 30s | Total Frames: 900 @ 30fps | Elements: 7 | Scenes: 5
Dimensions: 1920×1080 | Tone: Polished SaaS | Arc: B — App Intro
UI Source: TSX from HTML (dashboard.html, analytics.html)
 
---
 
### SCENE 1: HOOK
 
### ELEMENT 1 (0:00–0:03) | Frames: 0–90 | durationInFrames: 90
 
VO/Audio: "What if your entire business fit on one screen?"
Visual: Black background. Bold white text materializes. No product yet.
Shot Type: Kinetic typography — full screen
Source: Remotion
 
Text Overlay: "WHAT IF YOUR ENTIRE BUSINESS FIT ON ONE SCREEN?"
Text Animation: Velocity-slide (line by line, 8 frames apart)
Transition to next: Fade to dark
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Line 1: translateX interpolate([0, 10], [-600, 0]), Easing.out(Easing.cubic), clamp
  - Line 2: same, delayed 8 frames
  - Hold frames 30–80
  - Exit: opacity interpolate([75, 90], [1, 0])
  - Key hooks: interpolate, Easing
 
---
 
### SCENE 2: PRODUCT REVEAL
 
### ELEMENT 2 (0:03–0:07) | Frames: 90–210 | durationInFrames: 120
 
VO/Audio: "Meet Atlas."
Visual: Atlas logo springs into center on dark background. Tagline typewriters below.
Shot Type: Logo reveal — animation
Source: Remotion + brand asset (logo.svg)
 
Text Overlay: "ATLAS" (logo) + "Your business dashboard, reimagined."
Text Animation: Logo: spring pop. Tagline: typewriter starting frame 30.
Transition to next: Scale zoom into dashboard
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Logo scale: spring({ frame, fps, config: { stiffness: 120, damping: 12 } })
  - Glow burst: opacity interpolate([0, 4, 20], [0, 1, 0]) on radial gradient behind logo
  - Tagline typewriter: charsVisible = Math.floor(interpolate([30, 90], [0, tagline.length]))
  - Transition: scale interpolate([100, 120], [1, 1.3]) + opacity interpolate([110, 120], [1, 0])
  - Key hooks: spring, interpolate
 
---
 
### SCENE 3: FEATURE 1 — DASHBOARD
 
### ELEMENT 3 (0:07–0:13) | Frames: 210–390 | durationInFrames: 180
 
VO/Audio: "All your KPIs, live."
Visual: Full Atlas dashboard TSX UI materializes — panels slide in from edges. Chart draws itself. KPI numbers count up.
Shot Type: TSX UI — full dashboard
Source: TSX (from HTML) — ui/Dashboard.tsx
 
Component: Dashboard
Highlight: KPI stat cards (top row) then main chart
Interaction: Panels slide in staggered, chart line draws, numbers count up
 
Text Overlay: "LIVE KPIs · REAL-TIME" (top-left, small, fades in frame 60)
Text Animation: Fade
Transition to next: Slow push-in toward chart panel
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - dashboardProgress: interpolate([0, 30], [0, 1]) — overall entry
  - statCard[i]: spring({ frame: frame - i * 8, fps, config: { stiffness: 100, damping: 18 } }) — stagger
  - chartProgress: interpolate([40, 150], [0, 1]) — line draws
  - kpiValue: Math.round(interpolate([20, 110], [0, targetValue]))
  - Camera push: scale interpolate([90, 180], [1, 1.18]), translateY interpolate([90, 180], [0, -60])
  - Key hooks: spring, interpolate, useCurrentFrame
 
---
 
### ELEMENT 4 (0:13–0:17) | Frames: 390–510 | durationInFrames: 120
 
VO/Audio: "Drill into anything."
Visual: Camera zooms into a single chart bar. A tooltip appears. Sub-breakdown panel slides in from right.
Shot Type: TSX UI — close-up zoom on chart
Source: TSX (from HTML) — ui/Chart.tsx + ui/DrilldownPanel.tsx
 
Component: Chart (with DrilldownPanel)
Highlight: Single bar → tooltip → side panel
Interaction: Tooltip fade in, panel slides from right
 
Text Overlay: NONE
Transition to next: Wipe right
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Zoom: scale interpolate([0, 40], [1.18, 2.2]), translateX/Y toward bar target position
  - Tooltip: opacity interpolate([30, 45], [0, 1]), translateY interpolate([30, 45], [8, 0])
  - Panel: translateX interpolate([50, 80], [400, 0]), opacity interpolate([50, 65], [0, 1])
  - Key hooks: interpolate, Easing.out
 
---
 
### SCENE 4: FEATURE 2 — COLLABORATION
 
### ELEMENT 5 (0:17–0:22) | Frames: 510–660 | durationInFrames: 150
 
VO/Audio: "Your whole team, in sync."
Visual: Atlas team view TSX UI — user avatars appear, activity feed updates in real time, a comment thread slides in.
Shot Type: TSX UI — team activity view
Source: TSX (from HTML) — ui/TeamView.tsx
 
Component: TeamView
Highlight: Activity feed + comment thread
Interaction: Feed items appear staggered, avatars pop in, comment slides from bottom
 
Text Overlay: "TEAM · REAL-TIME COLLABORATION"
Text Animation: Slide-up, frame 80
Transition to next: Cut
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Avatar[i]: spring({ frame: frame - i * 6, fps, config: { stiffness: 180, damping: 16 } })
  - Feed item[i]: translateY interpolate([i*8, i*8+20], [20, 0]), opacity interpolate([i*8, i*8+15], [0, 1])
  - Comment panel: translateY interpolate([70, 100], [80, 0]), opacity interpolate([70, 85], [0, 1])
  - Key hooks: spring, interpolate
 
---
 
### SCENE 5: CTA
 
### ELEMENT 6 (0:22–0:27) | Frames: 660–810 | durationInFrames: 150
 
VO/Audio: "Try Atlas free — no setup required."
Visual: Dark background, logo centered, CTA button pulses, URL below.
Shot Type: Animation — CTA card
Source: Remotion
 
Text Overlay: "TRY ATLAS FREE" + "atlas.io" below
Text Animation: CTA: spring pop. URL: typewriter.
Transition to next: Hold
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - CTA text: spring({ frame, fps, config: { stiffness: 140, damping: 12 } }) on scale
  - Button glow: filter drop-shadow with Math.sin(frame/10)*4 + 10 radius
  - URL typewriter: interpolate([30, 70], [0, url.length])
  - Key hooks: spring, Math.sin, interpolate
 
---
 
### ELEMENT 7 (0:27–0:30) | Frames: 810–900 | durationInFrames: 90
 
VO/Audio: [music fade out]
Visual: Logo + tagline hold. Clean end card.
Shot Type: Static hold
Source: Remotion
 
Text Overlay: "ATLAS · atlas.io"
Text Animation: None — already visible from Element 6
Transition to next: None (end)
 
Remotion Animation Spec:
  - Subtle logo breathe: scale = 1 + Math.sin(frame / 20) * 0.006
  - Key hooks: Math.sin
 
---
 
### PRODUCTION NOTES
Music: Minimal electronic, 110BPM, clean and focused, fades last 5s
Pacing: Medium — confident, not rushed. Breathing room in Feature scenes.
Color: Brand-matched (extract from design-tokens.ts)
Style: Polished SaaS — sharp, no decorative clutter
Captions: Required (LinkedIn 85% muted) — burn in white text, bottom center
 
### ASSETS NEEDED
- [ ] Logo: atlas-logo.svg
- [ ] Audio: background.mp3 (110BPM, 30s)
- [ ] Font: from design-tokens.ts (via @remotion/google-fonts)
- [ ] HTML files: dashboard.html, analytics.html (already provided → run html-to-tsx pipeline)
 
